Your `theater` class has a method called `registerUser()` which creates an instance of `registeredUser` and returns it. `registeredUser` similarly has a method called `addUserData()` which creates an instance of `userData` and returns it. The names for these methods are misleading because neither of them add or register a user with the outer class. Instead, they both just create an instance and return it.

I don&#39;t see a reason to separate `registeredUser` from `userData`. You should just create a `User` class with all the fields necessary for a user. You should also add a field to the `theater` class to keep track of all of its users. For example, you could do:
```
class theater {
